SIMPLE: gumption
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gumption
<hw>Gump"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>gom</ets>,
<ets>gome</ets>, attention; akin to AS. <ets>ge⟦oacute⟧mian</ets>,
<ets>gyman</ets>, to regard, observe, <ets>gyme</ets> care, OS.
<ets>gomean</ets> to heed, Goth. <ets>gaumjan</ets> to see,
notice.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Capacity; shrewdness; common sense.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark><-- in MW10 marked as chiefly dial. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One does not have <qex>gumption</qex> till one has been properly
cheated.</q> <rj><qau>Lord Lytton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Paint.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The art of
preparing colors.</def> <au>Sir W. Scott.</au></p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Megilp.</def> <au>Fairholt.</au></p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>initiative; resourcefulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Courage; guts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>gumptious</ent>⟦br⟧
